main event: A bright, well-defined object was observed in the sky over Duluth, Minnesota on November 3, 1966, which changed shape and did not follow a regular course.
interesting points: The object was yellowish-white in color and one-twentieth the size of the full moon.
The object moved erratically and disappeared and reappeared at times.
There were no visible stars in the sky due to the brightness of the object.
The observer used an 8-power telescope to observe the object.
The observation lasted for almost 2 hours.
sighted object: a bright, changing object in the sky
